# Example Strava Cookie Formats
# Copy this file to .strava_cookies and update with your real cookie
# The tool supports both formats below - choose whichever is easier!

# ============================================================
# Format 1: Raw Cookie String (EASIEST - Just Copy/Paste!)
# ============================================================
# Simply copy the entire Cookie header from your browser DevTools
# and paste it here. That's it!
#
# Steps:
#   1. Open Chrome, log into strava.com
#   2. F12 → Network tab
#   3. Click any strava.com request
#   4. Copy the entire "Cookie" header value
#   5. Paste below (remove the # comment)
#
# Example:
# _strava4_session=your_session_value_here; CloudFront-Policy=xxx; CloudFront-Signature=yyy

# ============================================================
# Format 2: JSON Array (Structured)
# ============================================================
# Use this if you prefer structured data or only have the session value
#
# [
#   {
#     "name": "_strava4_session",
#     "value": "your_session_value_here",
#     "domain": ".strava.com"
#   }
# ]

# ============================================================
# How to Get Your Cookie:
# ============================================================
# Chrome DevTools Method:
#   1. Visit strava.com and log in
#   2. Press F12 (open DevTools)
#   3. Go to Network tab
#   4. Refresh the page or click around
#   5. Click any request to strava.com
#   6. Find "Request Headers" section
#   7. Look for "Cookie:" header
#   8. Copy the entire value (everything after "Cookie: ")
#   9. Paste here using Format 1
#
# Alternative - Application Tab Method:
#   1. F12 → Application tab
#   2. Left sidebar: Storage → Cookies → https://www.strava.com
#   3. Find "_strava4_session" cookie
#   4. Copy the "Value" field
#   5. Use Format 2 with just this value

# ============================================================
# Security Notes:
# ============================================================
# - This file is in .gitignore - it won't be committed
# - Your cookie grants full access to your Strava account
# - Cookies typically expire after hours/days
# - Get a fresh cookie if you see 401 Unauthorized errors
# - Never share this file or commit it to version control
